To create new tables in anahita without packages (Not Working Yet)(NOT A PERMANENT SOLUTION)
	You must update code in multiple locations:
		1.anahita/src/components/com_anahita/schemas/migrations/19.php
			-insert create table commands where appropriate
		2.anahita/vendor/anahita-platform/installation/sql/schema.sql
			-insert create table commands in the document in correct order
		3.anahita/src/components/com_anahita/schemas/migrations.php
			- add table names to tables array

To create new tables in anahita with packages (Working)(Permanent Solution)
		-(Use Tester Package as example)	
	1. Create a new package directory in Packages
	2. Follow package structure and include correct table Schemas
	3. php anahita package:install yourcomponentname
	4. To verify that it installed correctly
		-package will be displayed in the an_components table
		-yourcomponentname will be its own table in anahita DB
	

To Update tables in anahita (tables that already exist)
	1. If you've added a table to the Database using a package it will be displayed within the an_components table
	2. Remove your table from Database
		-Drop table tablename;
	3. Uninstall Package
		-php anahita package:\uninstall packagename
	4. when you update your package you need to first remove your package from an_components Table in Database
		- this is because anahita checks for the componentName in an_components if it already exists it will not add
		- delete from an_components where name='componentName';
	5. then re-install updated package to anahita
		- php anahita package:install yourcomponentname


To View Columns in Table
	1. select column_name from information_schema.columns where table_name='nameOfTable'




